'''Kamitsukeno no Michichi''' (上毛野 三千) was a [[nobility|nobleman]] during the [[Asuka period]] of Japan. His {{ill|Kabane|ja|カバネ}} title was {{ill|Kimi (kabane)|ja|キミ}}. He held the Rank of {{ill|Ōkinoshita|ja|大錦下}}.
== Biography == The {{ill|Kamitsukeno clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan}}, to which Michichi belonged, is noted in the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}} under the Left and Right Imperial Descendants sections, identifying them as descendants of Emperor {{ill|Sujin|ja|崇神天皇}}'s eldest son, {{ill|Toyokiiribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto}}.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' Emperor Sujin, 48th Year, 1st Month, 10th Day.</ref>
